column2: HOW IS A UNIVERSITY ID ISSUED TO FIRST TIME STUDENTS
column5:
After paying the tuition fees follow the following steps#Newline
    #Newline
  1. Submit a personal photo on which the students name and university number are clearly written on the back to the Identity Office #Newline Department of Student Services and Welfare Deanship of Student Affairs First Floor
    2. #Newline
  2. #Newline Entering the students electronic portal to ensure the following information#Newline
      #Newline
    • #Newline The name in English from three syllables and then the amendment if any through the Admission and Registration Unit#Newline Ensure the phone number and address of the student place of residence and the amendment#Newline if any is made through the Deanship of Student Affairs Department of Student Services and Welfare First Floor#Newline
      • #Newline
    • And then work on the last steps which is to approve the information through the student portal
      • #Newline
    • The ID is submitted during the semester in which the student is registered through the ID Distribution Center of Cairo Amman Bank
      • #Newline
    #Newline
    3. #Newline

column2: WHEN THE UNIVERSITY ID IS LOST THE FOLLOWING STEPS ARE FOLLOWED
column5:
#Newline
  1. Visit the ID Office at the Deanship of Student Affairs
    2. #Newline
  2. Student Services and Welfare Department to report the identity in case of loss#Comma and information about students is taken
    3. #Newline
  3. then the information is sent to Cairo Amman Bank for issuance and the student reviews the bank after two weeks.
    4. #Newline
